               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> Indenture made <origDate notBefore="1517-04-22" notAfter="1518-04-21">27 October, 9 Hen. VIII</origDate>, between 
               <persName>
                           <forename>George</forename> 
                           <surname>Hastings</surname>, kt., lord <placeName role="lord" key="place_110078">Hastings</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               of the one part, and <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Sacheverell</surname>, kt.</persName>, 
               and the <persName>rt. hon. lady <forename>Marye</forename>, lady Hungerford</persName>, 
               &amp;c., mother of the said lord and wife to the said
               sir Richard, of the other part, witnesseth that in consideration of the great charges
               &amp;c. which the said sir Richard and lady Mary have been put to in maintaining and
               supporting the honor of the said lord, he grants to them and their heirs the manor of
               <placeName type="manor" key="place_108678">Aller in the county of Somerset</placeName>, with power to assign
               20 marks yearly for an almoner for poor people to pray for their souls.
               Signed, R. Sacheverell<!--TODO, unclear annotation: mare Hungreford Brottreaux Mollens-->
               . </p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
